This paper involves a task allocation and scheduling problem with a team of human operators and robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm presented also involves approximation ratios, which suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms (cs.AI, cs.DS). The problem also involves coordination and control of multiple agents, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of approximation algorithms and analysis suggests a focus on theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
